column5: Variable Selection:  For my model I chose minutes played, field goal attempts and 3 point attempts.
Answer 1:  My model has an R square of .98 which is very high therefore it is a very good model for predicting the amount of points a player would score.
Answer 2: The high R square value and the exremely low p values for my variables would indicate that my model is statistically reliable.

Answer 3:  The coeffecients represent the three variables I selected of minutes played, field goal attempts and three point attempts.  The coefficient for my filed goal attempts is 1.375, this means that for each additional attempt a players predicted score increases by 1.375 points.  Ironnically three point attempts and time in game both have negative coefficients, so the longer a player plays and the more three point attempts they make the lower the predicted points
